"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Credible tourism files usually contain realistic details."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with insufficient funds for itinerary?","options":["If the trip costs exceed available funds, the officer may doubt both purpose and ability to leave.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Financial evidence must fit the proposed stay."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with recent job resignation?","options":["Leaving employment shortly before applying can weaken ties and raise migration concerns.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"The officer evaluates circumstances at the time of decision."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with inconsistent host relationship?","options":["Conflicting claims about the host relationship can damage credibility.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Relationship evidence should align with forms, invitation letters, and civil records."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with hidden work plans?","options":["Evidence suggesting the visitor will work without authorization can lead to refusal.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Visitors must not enter the Canadian labour market without proper authorization."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with medical inadmissibility?","options":["A required medical exam can reveal inadmissibility concerns or delay the application.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Visitor eligibility includes health screening where required."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with criminal history?","options":["Even old offences can require careful admissibility analysis before a TRV is approved.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Criminality is separate from whether the visit purpose is genuine."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with large unexplained deposits?","options":["Sudden deposits may be discounted unless the source is documented.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Officers look for stable, legitimate funds."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with conflicting travel dates?","options":["Different dates across forms, invitation letters, and bookings can make the file appear unreliable.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Consistency helps the officer understand the plan."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with previous long stays in Canada?","options":["Repeated long stays may make the officer question whether the person is living in Canada as a visitor.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Patterns of use matter even when each entry was lawful."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with lack of return ticket?","options":["A missing return ticket is not automatic refusal, but no return plan can contribute to temporary intent concerns.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"The officer needs confidence the stay is temporary."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with minor travelling with one parent?","options":["Missing consent from the other parent can raise child protection and custody concerns.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Consent and custody documents should be clear."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with purpose changing after submission?","options":["A materially changed purpose should be updated with evidence or the original file may become misleading.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Officers decide based on the record before them."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with invitation from a person without status?","options":["A host with no valid Canadian status may weaken the invitation and raise credibility questions.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Host circumstances are relevant when they support the visit."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with template refusal response?","options":["A reapplication that does not address the specific refusal grounds is unlikely to satisfy the officer.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"The new file should add material evidence or explanation."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with dual intent for visitors?","options":["A possible future PR plan is allowed only if the applicant still shows they will leave if required.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Dual intent does not cancel the temporary resident test."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with documents with authenticity concerns?","options":["Questionable bank, job, or civil documents can lead to refusal or a procedural fairness process.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Authenticity issues are treated seriously."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with weak economic establishment?","options":["No employment, assets, studies, or regular income can make it harder to prove return incentives.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Economic establishment is a common TRV risk factor."},{"level":3,"question":"Officer perspective in a temporary resident visa visitor application: what is the key issue with airport questioning?","options":["Inconsistent answers at the port of entry can lead to refusal of entry despite having a visa.","It is harmless because officers approve cases when the applicant is polite.","It can be fixed after refusal by sending documents to the visa office informally.","It matters only at the airport and not during the paper or online review."],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"A TRV permits travel for examination; CBSA still decides admission."}],"donts":{"dos":["Document strong ties—employment, property, family obligations","Align purpose, cover letter, and supporting documents","Explain funds source with 4–6 month bank history","Disclose all prior refusals with changed circumstances","Verify current IRCC fees before quoting client"],"donts":["Do not guarantee approval regardless of profile strength","Do not submit without signed client checklist where policy requires","Do not use purpose-inconsistent documents (tourism file with business-only papers)","Do not hide previous refusals from Canada or other countries","Do not miss biometrics deadline after BIL"],"mistakes":["Generic cover letter not explaining return intent","Large unexplained recent bank deposits","Missing employer leave letter for salaried applicants","Overstated trip duration without credible reason","Blurry scans or name mismatches across documents"]},"sampleDocs":[{"title":"Sample passport bio page (mock)","description":"Show clients which pages to scan — MRZ visible, no glare, full spread.","mimeType":"image/jpeg","docKind":"identity"},{"title":"Sample bank statement (mock)","description":"6-month statement with name, account number, and closing balance — explain seasoning.","mimeType":"application/pdf","docKind":"financial"},{"title":"Sample invitation / sponsor letter (mock)","description":"Host details, relationship, accommodation, and duration of stay.","mimeType":"application/pdf","docKind":"supporting"},{"title":"Sample travel itinerary (mock)","description":"Flights, hotels, and day-wise plan for visitor visa credibility.","mimeType":"application/pdf","docKind":"supporting"},{"title":"Sample employment / NOC letter (mock)","description":"Employer letter confirming leave, role, salary, and return to India.","mimeType":"application/pdf","docKind":"employment"},{"title":"Sample property / ties document (mock)","description":"Sale deed or tax receipt — explain home-country ties.","mimeType":"application/pdf","docKind":"financial"}],"navBucket":"visa"}'::jsonb, updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'b2000001-0001-4000-8000-000000000011';

UPDATE public.service_library
SET academy_metadata = '{"displayName":"Canada – Spouse / Partner Sponsorship","shortDescription":"IRCC family sponsorship · Inland & outland · PR pathway for spouses","version":"v1.0","versionStatus":"Live","reviewStatus":"active","updatedLabel":"Updated 6 Jun 2026","learningLevel":"Advanced","learningMinutes":25,"policyAlert":{"active":true,"date":"6 Jun 2026","summary":"Confirm current IRCC spousal sponsorship fees (principal + right of permanent residence fee) on canada.ca before quoting."},"alert":{"title":"Genuine relationship evidence","body":"Officers scrutinise relationship genuineness. Weak or inconsistent evidence is a leading refusal factor—build a chronological, document-backed story."},"tags":[{"label":"Active service","variant":"success"},{"label":"Relationship proof critical","variant":"warning"},{"label":"12–18 months","variant":"neutral"},{"label":"Online – IRCC","variant":"neutral"}],"chips":[{"label":"12–18 months processing","variant":"neutral"},{"label":"CAD $1,150+ fees","variant":"neutral"},{"label":"Genuine relationship","variant":"warning"},{"label":"Inland or outland","variant":"success"}],"kpis":[{"label":"Processing time","value":"12–18m","sub":"Varies by stream and office","tone":"primary"},{"label":"Government fee","value":"CAD $1,150+","sub":"+ biometrics, medical","tone":"warning"},{"label":"Our approval rate","value":"91%","sub":"~82% industry benchmark","tone":"success"},{"label":"Required docs","value":"18","sub":"+ relationship evidence","tone":"violet"},{"label":"Consultancy fee","value":"See fee tab","sub":"+ govt & third-party","tone":"primary"}],"about":[{"label":"Description","value":"Family class sponsorship allowing a Canadian citizen or permanent resident to sponsor a spouse, common-law, or conjugal partner for permanent residence. Outland applications processed from abroad; inland if partner is in Canada."},{"label":"Eligible applicants","value":"Legally married or qualifying common-law/conjugal relationship · Sponsor meets income/residency requirements · Genuine relationship · Medical and security clearances"},{"label":"Inland vs outland","value":"Outland: partner outside Canada, can visit during processing. Inland: partner in Canada; may qualify for open work permit while awaiting decision.","warning":true},{"label":"Key authority","value":"Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC)"},{"label":"After approval","value":"Partner receives COPR and completes landing. Maintain relationship genuineness obligations; misrepresentation has serious consequences."}],"eligibility":[{"criterion":"Sponsor is Canadian citizen or PR aged 18+","met":true,"note":"Verify sponsor status and residency obligations"},{"criterion":"Legally valid marriage or qualifying relationship","met":true,"note":"Marriage certificate; common-law needs 12+ months cohabitation proof"},{"criterion":"Genuine relationship evidence","met":true,"note":"Photos, communication, financial mingling, visits"},{"criterion":"Sponsor not in default of prior sponsorship undertakings","met":true},{"criterion":"Medical exam completed","met":false,"note":"Panel physician after instructions"},{"criterion":"Police certificates as required","met":false,"note":"Based on residence history"},{"criterion":"Biometrics completed","met":false,"note":"Both sponsor and applicant if required"}],"redFlagsBanner":"If refused for relationship genuineness, do not reapply with the same weak evidence. Rebuild a chronological, verifiable relationship narrative first.","redFlags":[{"title":"Weak relationship evidence","description":"Few photos, no communication logs, short relationship timeline, or inconsistent stories.","fix":"Chronological timeline; chat/call logs; joint finances; visit stamps; affidavits from family","severity":"Very common"},{"title":"Marriage of convenience suspicion","description":"Large age gap without explanation, met only days before marriage, or prior failed sponsorships.","fix":"Honest narrative; explain how relationship developed; strong third-party support","severity":"High"},{"title":"Incomplete sponsor eligibility","description":"Sponsor on social assistance, prior undertaking default, or not meeting residency for PR sponsors.","fix":"Verify sponsor eligibility checklist on canada.ca before fee collection","severity":"High"},{"title":"Wrong stream (inland vs outland)","description":"Applied inland when partner cannot remain legally in Canada, or outland without travel plan clarity.","fix":"Assess partner''s current status; choose stream with legal counsel if complex","severity":"Common"},{"title":"Missing or inconsistent forms","description":"IMM forms incomplete, dates mismatch across documents, or unsigned declarations.","fix":"Cross-check all dates; dual review before upload","severity":"Common"},{"title":"Undisclosed prior relationships or refusals","description":"Hidden prior marriages, refusals, or misrepresentation history.","fix":"Full disclosure; address changed circumstances in cover letter","severity":"High"}],"faqs":[{"q":"Can we guarantee PR approval for a genuine marriage?","a":"No. Even genuine couples can face requests for additional evidence or refusal if documentation is weak. We improve file quality but never promise approval."},{"q":"Inland or outland—which is faster?","a":"Timelines vary and change. Outland may allow partner to visit during processing; inland may offer open work permit eligibility. Assess case-by-case."},{"q":"How much relationship evidence is enough?","a":"No fixed amount—officers want a credible chronological story: how you met, communication, visits, marriage, shared life plans. Quality over quantity."},{"q":"Can a sponsored spouse work while waiting?","a":"Inland applicants may apply for open work permit after AIP stage in many cases. Verify current IRCC rules at time of counseling."},{"q":"What if marriage is recent?","a":"Recent marriages need stronger evidence—communication history before marriage, visit records, photos, and explanation of relationship development."},{"q":"Does sponsor need minimum income?","a":"Spousal sponsorship generally has no LICO requirement for spouse/partner/child, but sponsor must not be on social assistance (except disability) and must meet undertaking obligations."},{"q":"What happens after refusal?","a":"Review refusal letter carefully. Options may include appeal (IAD) for in-Canada refusals in some cases, or reapplication with stronger evidence."},{"q":"Are common-law partners eligible?","a":"Yes, if they have cohabited continuously for at least 12 months. Evidence of shared residence is essential."}],"compliance":["Spousal sponsorship requires licensed RCIC or lawyer for paid representation in Canada—confirm credentials","Client service agreement and consent must be on file before submission","Never guarantee PR approval; marriage alone does not ensure success","Fee quotes must separate consultancy, government, medical, and biometrics"],"proTips":["Build a relationship timeline document before collecting forms","Cross-check every date across marriage cert, photos, and travel history","For recent marriages, include pre-marriage communication evidence","Verify sponsor eligibility before taking full fees","Save relationship evidence binder separately for RFI responses"],"postApproval":["Send COPR and landing instructions to client in writing","Remind client of PR card application after landing","Explain sponsor undertaking period (typically 3 years for spouse)","Register for post-landing settlement briefing if offered"],"performance":{"ourRate":91,"industryRate":82,"stats":[{"label":"Files this year","value":"47"},{"label":"Approved","value":"43"},{"label":"Refused","value":"3"},{"label":"Withdrawn","value":"1"}]},"approvalFactors":[{"label":"Our rate vs industry","ours":91,"benchmark":82},{"label":"Relationship evidence quality","ours":88,"benchmark":72},{"label":"Form accuracy","ours":94,"benchmark":78},{"label":"Complete checklist first submit","ours":90,"benchmark":75}],"timeline":[{"weeks":"1–2","title":"Counseling, sponsor eligibility check, fee agreement"},{"weeks":"2–6","title":"Relationship evidence collection, forms, medical/police"},{"weeks":"6–8","title":"Quality review & IRCC submission"},{"weeks":"8–12","title":"Acknowledgement of receipt (AOR)"},{"weeks":"12–18m","title":"Processing to decision (varies)"}],"relatedServices":[{"label":"Canada – Visitor Visa (TRV)","libraryId":""},{"label":"Canada – Express Entry PR","libraryId":""},{"label":"Canada – Work Permit","libraryId":""}],"changelog":[{"version":"v1.0","date":"6 Jun 2026","author":"Service Library","summary":"Initial counselor content for Canada spousal sponsorship with 2026 fee notes."}],"staffNotes":[{"author":"Documentation team","date":"6 Jun 2026","text":"Arranged marriages need extra care—build pre-marriage communication evidence and family affidavits without appearing fabricated."},{"author":"Quality","date":"6 Jun 2026","text":"Mandatory dual review for all spousal files—date mismatches are the top internal QA finding."}],"resources":[{"title":"IRCC — Sponsor your spouse, partner or child","url":"https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/immigrate-canada/family-sponsorship/spouse-partner-children.html","description":"Official sponsorship requirements and application guide"},{"title":"IRCC — Check processing times","url":"https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/application/check-processing-times.html","description":"Current spousal sponsorship processing estimates"},{"title":"IRCC — Application fees","url":"https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/immigration-citizenship-application-fees.html","description":"Current sponsorship and right of PR fees"},{"title":"IRCC — Biometrics","url":"https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/campaigns/biometrics/facts.html","description":"Biometrics requirements for family class"},{"title":"IRCC — Medical exams","url":"https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/application/medical-police/medical-exams.html","description":"When and how to complete immigration medical exam"}],"quiz":[{"question":"What is a leading refusal reason in spousal sponsorship?","options":["Passport colour","Weak or inconsistent relationship evidence","Hotel bookings","Language test scores"],"correctIndex":1,"explanation":"Officers must be satisfied the relationship is genuine."},{"question":"Common-law partners must generally show:","options":["1 month cohabitation","12+ months continuous cohabitation","No evidence needed","Only wedding photos"],"correctIndex":1,"explanation":"IRCC requires at least 12 months of continuous cohabitation for common-law."},{"question":"Can counselors guarantee PR for genuine marriages?","options":["Yes, always","No, never guarantee approval","Yes, if married 5+ years","Yes, if sponsor is citizen"],"correctIndex":1,"explanation":"Firm policy: never guarantee immigration outcomes."},{"question":"Inland sponsorship may allow the partner to:","options":["Skip medical exam","Apply for open work permit in many cases while awaiting decision","Work without any permit immediately","Leave Canada permanently without impact"],"correctIndex":1,"explanation":"Inland stream has specific work permit options—verify current rules."},{"question":"Before submission, counselors must verify:","options":["Sponsor eligibility and complete relationship timeline","Only marriage certificate","Client''s school marks","Hotel reservations in Canada"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Sponsor eligibility and relationship narrative are foundational."}],"donts":{"dos":["Build chronological relationship timeline with verifiable evidence","Verify sponsor eligibility before fee collection","Cross-check all dates across forms and documents","Disclose all prior relationships, refusals, and marriages","Prepare for RFI with evidence binder ready"],"donts":["Do not guarantee PR approval for any relationship type","Do not submit fabricated photos or communication logs","Do not hide prior failed sponsorships or refusals","Do not choose inland/outland without assessing partner''s legal status","Do not quote fees without checking current IRCC fee page"],"mistakes":["Few relationship photos with no context or dates","Date mismatches between marriage cert and application forms","Missing police certificates for required countries","Sponsor on social assistance without eligibility check","Generic relationship letter not matching actual timeline"]},"sampleDocs":[{"title":"Sample passport bio page (mock)","description":"Show clients which pages to scan — MRZ visible, no glare, full spread.","mimeType":"image/jpeg","docKind":"identity"},{"title":"Sample marriage certificate (mock)","description":"Registered marriage proof — explain translation and notarization if needed.","mimeType":"application/pdf","docKind":"relationship"},{"title":"Sample relationship timeline & photos guide (mock)","description":"Collage layout for chat logs, travel photos, and ceremony pictures.","mimeType":"application/pdf","docKind":"relationship"},{"title":"Sample sponsor / undertaking letter (mock)","description":"Sponsor income, accommodation, and maintenance commitment.","mimeType":"application/pdf","docKind":"financial"},{"title":"Sample bank statement (mock)","description":"6-month statement with name, account number, and closing balance — explain seasoning.","mimeType":"application/pdf","docKind":"financial"},{"title":"Sample chat / communication evidence (mock)","description":"Redacted WhatsApp or email excerpts — privacy-safe specimen.","mimeType":"image/jpeg","docKind":"relationship"}],"navBucket":"visa"}'::jsonb, updated_at = now()
WHERE id = 'b2000001-0001-4000-8000-000000000012';

UPDATE public.service_library
SET academy_metadata = '{"displayName":"Canada – Express Entry (Permanent Residence)","shortDescription":"IRCC Express Entry · FSW/CEC/FST · CRS score · ITA","version":"v2.0","versionStatus":"Live","reviewStatus":"active","updatedLabel":"Updated 6 Jun 2026","learningLevel":"Advanced","learningMinutes":30,"policyAlert":{"active":true,"date":"6 Jun 2026","summary":"Confirm current Express Entry profile fee and PR application fee on canada.ca. CRS cutoffs change each draw—never promise ITA."},"alert":{"title":"CRS score drives selection","body":"Express Entry is points-based. No ITA without meeting draw cutoff. Counsel on realistic CRS before taking PR application fees."},"tags":[{"label":"Active service","variant":"success"},{"label":"CRS assessment required","variant":"warning"},{"label":"6–12 months post-ITA","variant":"neutral"},{"label":"Online – IRCC","variant":"neutral"}],"chips":[{"label":"CRS-based selection","variant":"warning"},{"label":"CAD $1,525+ PR fee","variant":"neutral"},{"label":"ECA + language tests","variant":"success"},{"label":"No ITA guarantee","variant":"warning"}],"kpis":[{"label":"Processing time","value":"6–12m","sub":"After ITA received","tone":"primary"},{"label":"Government fee","value":"CAD $1,525+","sub":"PR application after ITA","tone":"warning"},{"label":"Our approval rate","value":"94%","sub":"~88% post-ITA benchmark","tone":"success"},{"label":"Required docs","value":"16","sub":"+ ECA, language, work ref","tone":"violet"},{"label":"Consultancy fee","value":"See fee tab","sub":"+ govt & ECA/tests","tone":"primary"}],"about":[{"label":"Description","value":"Federal economic immigration system managing FSW, CEC, and FST programs. Candidates create profile, receive CRS score, and apply for PR if invited (ITA)."},{"label":"Eligible applicants","value":"Meet FSW/CEC/FST criteria · Valid language tests · ECA for foreign education · Sufficient CRS score · Medical and police clearances"},{"label":"ITA not guaranteed","value":"Profile in pool does not guarantee invitation. CRS cutoffs vary per draw. PNP can add 600 points.","warning":true},{"label":"Key authority","value":"Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC)"},{"label":"After approval","value":"COPR issued; complete landing; apply for PR card. Meet residency obligations for citizenship pathway."}],"eligibility":[{"criterion":"Eligible program (FSW/CEC/FST)","met":true},{"criterion":"Language test (CLB minimum per program)","met":true},{"criterion":"ECA for foreign credentials (FSW)","met":true,"note":"WES/IQAS etc."},{"criterion":"CRS score competitive for recent draws","met":false,"note":"Assess against recent cutoffs"},{"criterion":"Work experience documented (NOC/TEER)","met":true},{"criterion":"Proof of funds (FSW/ FST if applicable)","met":true},{"criterion":"Medical and police completed after ITA","met":false}],"redFlagsBanner":"Without ITA, do not submit PR application. Improve CRS via language retake, ECA, PNP, or Canadian experience before expecting invitation.","redFlags":[{"title":"CRS below recent draw cutoffs","description":"Client expects ITA with non-competitive score.","fix":"Retake language for higher CLB; pursue PNP; gain Canadian work experience","severity":"Very common"},{"title":"Wrong NOC/TEER code","description":"Work experience coded incorrectly affecting points.","fix":"Verify TEER category against official duties and reference letters","severity":"Very common"},{"title":"Reference letter deficiencies","description":"Employer letters missing duties, hours, or dates.","fix":"Detailed reference on company letterhead matching NOC duties","severity":"Common"},{"title":"ECA not completed","description":"Foreign degree not assessed before profile.","fix":"Complete ECA from designated organisation","severity":"Common"},{"title":"Language scores expired","description":"IELTS/CELPIP older than 2 years at ITA.","fix":"Retake before accepting ITA if expiring","severity":"High"},{"title":"Misrepresentation risk","description":"Inflated experience or false documents.","fix":"Honest accurate profile—misrepresentation has permanent consequences","severity":"High"}],"faqs":[{"q":"Can we guarantee ITA or PR?","a":"No. CRS cutoffs change each draw. We improve profile quality but never promise ITA or approval."},{"q":"What CRS score needed?","a":"Varies each draw—check recent IRCC draw results. Category-based draws have different cutoffs."},{"q":"How to improve CRS?","a":"Higher language scores, additional education ECA, Canadian work experience, PNP nomination (+600), French language bonus."},{"q":"What is PNP?","a":"Provincial Nominee Program—province nomination adds 600 CRS points, virtually ensuring ITA."},{"q":"Processing after ITA?","a":"Typically 6 months standard for most EE applications—verify current IRCC processing times."},{"q":"Can spouse be included?","a":"Yes—spouse factors into CRS; include if beneficial to score."},{"q":"Proof of funds when?","a":"Required at ITA stage for FSW; amount per family size on canada.ca."},{"q":"What if ITA declined?","a":"Profile may re-enter pool if valid—assess options carefully."}],"compliance":["Client service agreement and consent must be on file before submission","Never guarantee visa or immigration approval; use approved-language only","Fee quotes must separate consultancy, government, and third-party costs","Paid RCIC representation requires valid CICC membership"],"proTips":["Calculate CRS at intake with official calculator","Verify TEER codes against NOC 2021","Secure detailed employer reference letters early","Monitor draw trends—set realistic expectations","PNP exploration if CRS below cutoff"],"postApproval":["Send COPR and landing checklist","Explain PR card application","Remind residency days for citizenship","Connect to settlement services"],"performance":{"ourRate":94,"industryRate":88,"stats":[{"label":"Files this year","value":"89"},{"label":"Approved","value":"84"},{"label":"Refused","value":"3"},{"label":"Withdrawn","value":"2"}]},"approvalFactors":[{"label":"Post-ITA approval","ours":94,"benchmark":88},{"label":"CRS assessment accuracy","ours":91,"benchmark":75},{"label":"Reference letter quality","ours":88,"benchmark":72},{"label":"First-submit completeness","ours":93,"benchmark":80}],"timeline":[{"weeks":"1–4","title":"CRS assessment, ECA, language tests"},{"weeks":"4–6","title":"Profile creation and pool entry"},{"weeks":"Variable","title":"Wait for ITA (CRS-dependent)"},{"weeks":"6–12m","title":"PR application processing after ITA"}],"relatedServices":[{"label":"Canada – PGWP","libraryId":""},{"label":"Canada – Work Permit","libraryId":""},{"label":"Canada – Spouse Visa","libraryId":""}],"changelog":[{"version":"v2.0","date":"6 Jun 2026","author":"Service Library","summary":"Added 75 levelled quiz questions (Level 1–3, 25+ each) and expanded counselor content."},{"version":"v1.0","date":"6 Jun 2026","author":"Service Library","summary":"Initial Express Entry PR counselor content."}],"staffNotes":[{"author":"Documentation team","date":"6 Jun 2026","text":"Never collect full PR fee before ITA—profile setup fee only until invitation received."}],"resources":[{"title":"IRCC — Express Entry","url":"https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/immigrate-canada/express-entry.html","description":"Official EE overview"},{"title":"IRCC — CRS tool","url":"https://www.cic.gc.ca/english/immigrate/skilled/crs-tool.asp","description":"CRS calculator"},{"title":"IRCC — Check scores","url":"https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/immigrate-canada/express-entry/submit-profile/rounds-invitations.html","description":"Recent draw results"},{"title":"IRCC — Processing times","url":"https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/application/check-processing-times.html","description":"Current estimates"},{"title":"IRCC — ECA","url":"https://www.canada.ca/en/immigration-refugees-citizenship/services/immigrate-canada/express-entry/education-assessed.html","description":"Education credential assessment"}],"quiz":[{"level":1,"question":"What is Express Entry?","options":["An online system for managing certain economic PR applications","A temporary visitor visa category","A school admissions system","A passport renewal service"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Express Entry manages profiles and applications for major federal economic programs."},{"level":1,"question":"Which federal programs are managed through Express Entry?","options":["FSW, CEC, and FST","A temporary visitor visa category","A school admissions system","A passport renewal service"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Express Entry includes Federal Skilled Worker, Canadian Experience Class, and Federal Skilled Trades."},{"level":1,"question":"What does CRS stand for?","options":["Comprehensive Ranking System","A temporary visitor visa category","A school admissions system","A passport renewal service"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"CRS is the points system used to rank candidates."},{"level":1,"question":"What is an ITA?","options":["Invitation to Apply","A temporary visitor visa category","A school admissions system","A passport renewal service"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"An ITA invites a candidate to submit a complete PR application."},{"level":1,"question":"What does FSW stand for?","options":["Federal Skilled Worker","A temporary visitor visa category","A school admissions system","A passport renewal service"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"FSW is a federal economic program managed through Express Entry."},{"level":1,"question":"What does CEC stand for?","options":["Canadian Experience Class","A temporary visitor visa category","A school admissions system","A passport renewal service"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"CEC is for candidates with qualifying Canadian skilled work experience."},{"level":1,"question":"What does FST stand for?","options":["Federal Skilled Trades","A temporary visitor visa category","A school admissions system","A passport renewal service"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"FST is the federal skilled trades program."},{"level":1,"question":"What can a provincial nomination do in Express Entry?","options":["Add significant CRS points","A temporary visitor visa category","A school admissions system","A passport renewal service"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"An enhanced nomination can add major CRS points and often leads to an ITA."},{"level":1,"question":"What is the Express Entry pool?","options":["Eligible candidate profiles waiting for draws","A temporary visitor visa category","A school admissions system","A passport renewal service"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Profiles in the pool are ranked against other candidates."},{"level":1,"question":"Which factors commonly affect CRS?","options":["Age, education, language, and work experience","A temporary visitor visa category","A school admissions system","A passport renewal service"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Core CRS factors include human capital and skill transferability criteria."},{"level":1,"question":"What is a language test used for?","options":["Proving English or French proficiency","A temporary visitor visa category","A school admissions system","A passport renewal service"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Approved language results affect eligibility and CRS."},{"level":1,"question":"What is an ECA used for?","options":["Comparing foreign education to Canadian standards","A temporary visitor visa category","A school admissions system","A passport renewal service"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"An ECA can be required for foreign education points and FSW eligibility."},{"level":1,"question":"What must exist before entering the pool?","options":["Eligibility for at least one Express Entry program","A temporary visitor visa category","A school admissions system","A passport renewal service"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"A candidate must meet a managed program''s criteria."},{"level":1,"questio