gibility before enrolling?","options":["Some DLI programs do not lead to a PGWP","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"A school can be a DLI while a specific program is still not PGWP eligible."},{"level":1,"question":"What future immigration advantage can PGWP work experience create?","options":["It can help build Canadian skilled work experience","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Canadian work experience can support future pathways such as Canadian Experience Class."},{"level":1,"question":"What status does a PGWP holder have in Canada?","options":["Temporary resident worker status","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"A PGWP does not itself make the holder a permanent resident."},{"level":1,"question":"Which program length is often too short for standard PGWP eligibility?","options":["A program shorter than eight months","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Programs below the minimum duration generally do not support PGWP issuance."},{"level":1,"question":"Who issues a PGWP?","options":["Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"IRCC assesses and issues work permits, including PGWPs."},{"level":1,"question":"What does PGWP stand for?","options":["Post-Graduation Work Permit","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"PGWP is the common abbreviation for Post-Graduation Work Permit."},{"level":1,"question":"Which condition is least typical for a PGWP?","options":["Being tied to one named employer","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"A PGWP is open and usually not employer-specific."},{"level":1,"question":"Why is the one-time nature of a PGWP important?","options":["A poor timing choice can affect future work and PR planning","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Since a PGWP is generally issued once, applicants should plan the timing carefully."},{"level":1,"question":"Which school outcome matters most for a PGWP application?","options":["Successful completion of the eligible credential","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"The application depends on proof that the applicant completed the eligible program."},{"level":1,"question":"What does an open work permit generally allow?","options":["Work for most employers without a separate LMIA","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Open work permits are not tied to a specific employer, though conditions still apply."},{"level":1,"question":"What should a student check on the official DLI list?","options":["Whether the institution and program support PGWP eligibility","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Official eligibility details help avoid enrolling in a non-qualifying program."},{"level":1,"question":"Which previous status is usually relevant before a PGWP?","options":["Study permit status","A visitor visa issued for tourism only","An employer-specific LMIA approval","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Most applicants