ith no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Financial evidence can support temporary resident assessment."},{"level":2,"question":"What is the purpose of a letter of explanation?","options":["To connect relationship, principal eligibility, and family plan","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"A concise explanation helps officers understand the basis for eligibility."},{"level":2,"question":"Why check medical exam requirements?","options":["Certain jobs or residence histories may require medicals","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Medical conditions can appear on open work permits."},{"level":2,"question":"What travel document may be needed in addition to OWP approval?","options":["A TRV or eTA, depending on nationality","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Work authorization and travel authorization are separate."},{"level":2,"question":"How should previous refusals be handled?","options":["Disclose them accurately and address the reasons","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Omissions can create misrepresentation concerns."},{"level":2,"question":"What if the principal''s job is not skilled enough under current rules?","options":["The spouse OWP may not qualify under worker-based criteria","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Worker-based eligibility depends on the principal''s qualifying occupation or category."},{"level":2,"question":"What if the student''s program is not eligible under current rules?","options":["The spouse OWP may be refused","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Student-based eligibility depends on program and policy criteria."},{"level":2,"question":"Why are children''s school plans relevant?","options":["Children may need study authorization or visitor status depending on age and province","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Dependent children require their own status analysis."},{"level":2,"question":"What should be uploaded for identity?","options":["Passport bio pages and civil status documents","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Identity documents anchor the application."},{"level":2,"question":"Why does the principal''s permit length matter?","options":["The spouse OWP validity often follows it","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"A short principal permit can limit the spouse permit."},{"level":2,"question":"What is a good final review step?","options":["Confirm relationship proof, principal eligibility, forms, fees, and status dates","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"A consistency review reduces avoidable refusal risks."},{"level":3,"question":"What is the risk of a non-genuine relationship finding?","options":["Refusal and possible misrepresentation concerns","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Relationship credibility is central and false claims are serious."},{"level":3,"question":"Why can C41 or C42 coding matter?","options":["The exemption code must match the principal applicant''s qualifying situation","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Wrong coding can confuse eligibility and processing."},{"level":3,"question":"What if the principal worker is between jobs?","options":["Spouse eligibility may be difficult without active qualifying employment","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Worker-based spouse eligibility often depends on current qualifying work."},{"level":3,"question":"Why can unpaid leave by the principal worker matter?","options":["It may raise questions about active employment","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Pay and employment records can affect eligibility analysis."},{"level":3,"question":"What if the principal student''s program changes?","options":["The spouse''s eligibility should be reassessed under current rules","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Program changes can affect student-based OWP eligibility."},{"level":3,"question":"Why is unauthorized work by the spouse risky?","options":["It can affect status, extensions, and future applications","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Work must match authorization and permit conditions."},{"level":3,"question":"What if the principal loses status?","options":["The spouse''s derivative eligibility and family status plan may be affected","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Derivative work permits depend on the principal''s valid qualifying status."},{"level":3,"question":"Why should family members avoid inconsistent address histories?","options":["Inconsistencies can