y can dependent children''s age matter?","options":["Dependency rules and available status options depend on age","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Children''s status must be assessed separately."},{"level":3,"question":"What if a child wants to work in Canada?","options":["They need their own work authorization if eligible","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"A parent''s spouse OWP does not automatically authorize child employment."},{"level":3,"question":"Why is medical restriction compliance important?","options":["Some open permits restrict work in health, childcare, or similar fields","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"A medical exam may be needed to remove certain restrictions."},{"level":3,"question":"What if the spouse works for an ineligible employer listed by IRCC?","options":["It can breach open work permit conditions","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Open permits still prohibit work for certain employers or sectors."},{"level":3,"question":"Why should applicants disclose separation or relationship breakdown?","options":["It may affect eligibility and truthfulness of the application","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"The relationship must be genuine and continuing where required."},{"level":3,"question":"What is a procedural fairness concern in spouse OWP files?","options":["Doubts about relationship genuineness or document authenticity","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"A PFL should be answered with precise evidence."},{"level":3,"question":"Why avoid template-only relationship letters?","options":["They may fail to prove the couple''s specific history","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Specific credible evidence is stronger than generic statements."},{"level":3,"question":"What if the principal switches from study to PGWP?","options":["The spouse''s eligibility should be reassessed under worker-spouse rules","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Changing principal status can change the spouse''s eligibility basis."},{"level":3,"question":"Why can timing matter when applying with a principal extension?","options":["A refusal or delay in the principal file can affect the spouse file","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Family applications are connected when eligibility is derivative."},{"level":3,"question":"How should conflicting marital-status records be handled?","options":["Correct and explain them with civil documents","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Unresolved conflicts can create credibility concerns."},{"level":3,"question":"What if the spouse''s passport expires before the requested permit period?","options":["The permit may be shortened to passport validity","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"IRCC generally cannot issue beyond passport expiry."},{"level":3,"question":"What is the best strategy for a complex spouse OWP file?","options":["Document the relationship, principal eligibility, status history, and child status needs","A closed LMIA work permit only","A visitor visa with no work rights","A permanent resident card"],"correctIndex":0,"explanation":"Complex family files need a complete evidence-based narrative."}],"donts":{"dos":["Verify principal applicant eligibility first","Collect strong relationship and identity evidence","Disclose prior refusals honestly","Coordinate passport and permit expiry dates","Explain temporary nature of OWP"],"donts":["Do not assess spouse file without principal documents","Do not rely only on marriage certificate","Do not promise work rights before approval","Do not hide refusals or relationship inconsistencies","Do not quote outdated spouse-of-student rules"],"mistakes":["Principal permit not eligible under current rules","Thin relationship evidence for recent marriage","Conflicting addresses or dates across forms","Missing open work permit holder fee","Applicant passport expiry shortens permit"]},"sampleDocs":[{"title":"Sample passport bio page (mock)","description":"Applicant and principal applicant identity pages.","mimeType":"image/jpeg","docKind":"identity"},{"title":"Sample marriage certificate (mock)","description":"Civil marriage proof with certified translation if needed.","mimeType":"application/pdf","docKind":"identity"},{"title":"Sample relationship timeline (mock)","description":"Chronology of meeting, engagement, marriage, visits, and shared milestones.","mimeType":"application/pdf","docKind":"relationship"},{"title":"Sample photos and communication log (mock)","description":"Representative relationship evidence organized by date.","mimeType":"application/pdf","docKind":"relationship"},{"title":"Sample principal work permit / study permit (mock)","description":"Principal applicant status document and expiry date.","mimeType":"application/pdf","docKind":"identity"},{"title":"Sample principal employment letter (mock)","description":"Employment confirmation for qualifying worker cases.","mimeType":"application/pdf","docKind":"employment"},{"title":"Sample principal enrolment lett